column5: IRON MAIDEN   Will return to Toronto on July 03 2010 to promote The Final Frontier their 15th studio Album Like em or not they Rock Hard and take no prisoners they do not compromise their values , its always full steam ahead Back up will be Dream Theater. For those that have never you should this is Metal at its finest played by some of the most professional musicians on the planet. Tickets go on sale March 13 2010  And of course the added bonus to this glorius event will be the Pike Fishing during the day prior to the sonic assualt, from a paddle boat or shore around OP    UP THE IRONS  So if you is goin to the show that day let me know we could hook up (in a fishing kind of way) get some fish , some street meat, and go to the show and get our frontal lobes tore out  Peter
YES YES YESW YES YES  YES ............
Right on !!!!!!! Hey Buster ill meet you there!!!! again.......

Enticing to make a road trip up there.  Ironic as well as ive just pulled them back up out of my CD collection lol  My 10 year old nephew has me playing Alexander the Great OVER AND OVER AND OVER LOL  He also doesnt understand the concept of Live after death.........he said, why is there people cheering on the CD, .......I said cuz its a live album. He didnt get the concept of recording and selling an album that they recorded at a concert lol
i thought I was gonna read an article about fixing rivets on my canoe.

Here's a heads-up of one to watch for. Not sure if it's going to be a "one of"  as everyone involved has day jobs, but I expect it to be the premier rock CD of this year. At 60 years old, I grew up with Clapton, Page and Beck as guitar heroes, Bonamassa is every bit as good IMHO, probably technically better.  http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermo...wsitemID=135451  Have fun at the show and play it LOUD.
Right on!!  We could all use a little more IRON in our diets..  Pete I think we're due for a brodown with beers brah!  HD
You too, EH!Instead of swearing in the shop we used to say.....BUCK ON!!!!!!  FYI when buck rivoting.
Extremely excited for this!  Their last appearance was godlike.  I'm game for some pre-show pike fishing too!
